                   BlogCool

                 a minimal blog application

                 shamelessly copied from flaskr and other sources


    ~ What is BlogCool?

      A sqlite powered blog application

    ~ How do I use it?

      1. install the app from the root of the project directory

         pip install --editable .

      2. Instruct flask to use the right application

         export FLASK_APP=blogcool

      3. now you can run blogcool:

         flask run

         the application will greet you on
         http://localhost:5000/

      4. BlogCool has a JSON API!

         http://localhost:5000/all
                -- returns all the blogposts ever created

         http://localhost:5000/author/{author}
                --  returns all blogposts by the specified author

         http://localhost:5000/category/{category}
                -- returns all blogposts in the specified category

